✅ 9. Folder-Level IAM & Policy Inheritance (Step-by-Step)

Goal:
Create a Folder, assign IAM roles at folder level, and verify policy inheritance across projects.

🔹 Step 0: Start Lab & Login
Click Start Lab
Open Google Cloud Console
Login using lab credentials
Accept terms → Skip 2FA → Continue
🔹 Step 1: Open IAM & Resource Manager

Go to:

Navigation Menu ☰ → IAM & Admin → Manage Resources
You will see:
Organization (if available)
Projects
🔹 Step 2: Create a Folder
Click + CREATE FOLDER
Enter:
Name: Test-Folder
Under Organization, select your organization (if available)
Click CREATE

✅ Folder created successfully

🔹 Step 3: Create a Project inside Folder

Go to:

Navigation Menu ☰ → IAM & Admin → Manage Resources
Click + CREATE PROJECT
Fill:
Project Name: test-project-1
Location → Select: Test-Folder
Click CREATE

👉 This ensures project is inside the folder

🔹 Step 4: Assign IAM Role at Folder Level

In Manage Resources, click your folder:

Test-Folder
Go to Permissions tab
Click GRANT ACCESS
Enter:
New principal: (Test user email)

Role:

Viewer / Editor / Storage Object Viewer
Click SAVE

✅ Role assigned at folder level

🔹 Step 5: Understand Policy Inheritance

👉 Important concept:

Folder → Project → Resource
Permissions flow downward automatically

So:

Folder IAM → applies to all projects inside it
🔹 Step 6: Verify Inheritance in Project

Go to:

IAM & Admin → IAM
Select your project (test-project-1)
Check IAM list:
You will see the user added at folder level

Role appears with:

Inherited from: Folder

✅ This confirms inheritance is working

🔹 Step 7: Test Access (Optional but Recommended)
Login as Test User
Try accessing:
Compute Engine
Storage
Verify:
Access matches assigned role
🔹 Step 8: Modify Role at Folder Level

Go back to folder:

Manage Resources → Test-Folder
Edit role (e.g., Viewer → Editor)
Save

👉 Now go to project IAM → role automatically updated

✅ Shows real-time inheritance

🔹 Step 9: Remove Access
In folder IAM:
Remove the test user
Check project IAM

👉 User will lose access everywhere

🎯 Key Concepts (Very Important for Exams)
Folder IAM applies to all child projects
IAM follows hierarchical structure
Inheritance reduces manual permission management
Always follow least privilege principle
